replies.msg:
The motivation seems different for different people. Young people from Mainland China in Canada are often very supportive of the CCP. I once had a girl in my class get offended because I was comparing the size of Taiwan to the size of South Korea. I didn't even say that Taiwan was a country and that was still too much for her.<br />
<br />
Older people tend to value harmony more than freedom I think. I know someone who is from Hong Kong who is against the protests simply because of the violence and disruption. She doesn't mind the CCP encroaching on Hong Kong because the way she puts it, &ldquo;it's their country.&rdquo;

